issue.title: [Question] InteractionDeadline giving me timeouts in my commands response
issue.body:
Hey,
I noted that my slash command for an integration that I have is taking more than 3s in general.
I'd like to know if I'm able to increase the timeout for this type of interaction, at least to 15 seconds.

I noted that the lib has InteractionDeadline config setup to 3s.

Is there a way to change this on my code? 

https://github.com/bwmarrin/discordgo/blob/1f0b57f110241f1edff78d639cdb36885aeb7e1d/interactions.go#L17

comment.body:
The 3 second response time enforced by Discord on the server side. You need to send an ack and then can post a follow up. 

Here is an example: https://github.com/avislash/nftstamper/blob/main/cartel/bot.go#L244

issue.title: Rate limit unmarchal error
issue.body:
After few weeks of running our bots without issues, we encountered this issue which caused us to be rate-limited by cloudflare:
```
[DG0] restapi.go:149:RequestWithLockedBucket() rate limit unmarchal error, invalid character '<' looking for beginning of value
```

comment.body: Again, any update on this? I'm also encountering these errors a lot.

issue.title: How to make RateLimit work in multiple process?
issue.body: I read through the code for the rate limiter section, and I noticed there may be some issues in a multi-process environment. The rate limiter relies on sync.mutex to acquire locks, which is on a process level. In a multi-process environment, wouldn't this cause problems where rate limits could be triggered too quickly?

issue.title: Where are the interfaces ?
issue.body: I want to mock, but I dont see any interfaces ? What should I do ?

comment.body: To mock HTTP requests to the API, you can replace default `Session.Client.Transport` with your own implementation or the one provided by something like [httpmock](https://github.com/jarcoal/httpmock).

issue.title: component  is not json marshalable
issue.body: I'm trying to do `json.marshal` with `Message`, but its `Components` is like : `MessageComponent` is an interface, thus in design, it just can't be marshaled? I have a gateway service need to marshal the message and send to other real processor services. I have needed info in the `MessageComponent` field.

comment.body:
Hi, you can probably do the following:

```go
var msg = "{...}" // your json serialized message
var message discordgo.Message
if err := message.UnmarshalJSON(msg); err != nil {
	panic(err)
}
```
